ABUJA – Dr. Ezra Yakusat, Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer of the Nigerian Export Promotion Council (NEPC) has urged Nigerians to embrace the export of products for economic empowerment, poverty reduction and foreign exchange earning. Yakusat who stated this in Abuja on Saturday during the walking and jogging exercise to create awareness about the economic importance of export, said the export of products, is the way for economic survival. Speaking about the significance of the Walking and Jogging exercise with the theme,”Export4Survival”, Yakusat explained that it has become an emergency call for Nigerians to embrace the export of products. Gani Adams To Nigerians In Diaspora: Shun Negative News, Develop… FG Restates Ban On Export Of Donkey Hide He said: “We are making a clarion call to Nigerians that the only way to go is to export. “If we want economic empowerment, foreign exchange, poverty alleviation, we need to export. “That is the way to go. Export for Survival is an emergency call for all Nigerians to export.” He assured that the NEPC was working assiduously to create an enabling environment for exporters, adding that the Council is currently working on the enactment of enabling laws to drive export. POLL He hinted that the Council would embark on the sensitisation of Nigerians across the country on the importance of export for national development. Also speaking, Francis Duru, a Nollywood actor, commended NEPC for the new initiative, noting that Nigeria’s overreliance on oil has done more harm than good for economic development. Duru noted that the creative industry holds enormous potential for the nation’s economy, adding that the sector could jump-start the economy. Another Nollywood actor, Ejike Asiegbu, underscored the need for Nigeria to harness its abundant human and material resources to defeat the poverty plaguing the country.